::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-2.png){width=672}
:::
:::


*Comment*: The seasonal pattern is noticeable, though not as prominent as for the primary sector. In most years, the sector's share is lowest in the third quarter. This could simply be the effect of the seasonal swings in the primary sector: When the primary sector's share rises, the other sectors' shares fall. After all, the shares must add up to 100%.


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-7-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### Tertiary Sector

*Importance*: Income generated in the Tertiary sector was 56.24 percent of GVA in the latest quarter. This can be compared with the Tertiary sector's 53.06 percent share of GVA over the full data period.


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
