## A Closer Look at the Primary Sector

### Agriculture, Forestry and Fishing

*Importance*: Income generated in the *Agriculture_plus* sector was 13.06 percent of GVA in the latest quarter. This can be compared with the Agriculture_plus sector's 15.9 percent share of GVA over the full data period.

Recall that the corresponding shares for the Primary sector were 15.32 percent and 18.58 percent, respectively.


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-10-1.png){width=672}
:::

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-10-2.png){width=672}
:::
:::


*Comment*: Note that the seasonal pattern in *Agriculture, Forestry and Fishing* is very similar to that in the Primary sector as a whole. This is not surprising because most of the Primary sector is Agriculture, Forestry and Fishing while *Mining and Quarrying* has a small residual share.

Note also that Agriculture, Forestry and Fishing is in a long-term relative decline.


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-11-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### Mining and Quarrying

*Importance*: Income generated in the *Mining_plus* sector was 2.25 percent of GVA in the latest quarter. This can be compared with the Mining_plus sector's 2.68 percent share of GVA over the full data period.

Recall that the corresponding shares for the Primary sector were 15.32 percent and 18.58 percent, respectively.


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-12-1.png){width=672}
:::

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-12-2.png){width=672}
